# GitHub Personal Access Token used at BUILD time to draw the per-repo
# "commits per day" line graph on /github (includes private repos as a
# single aggregated "Private" line — no private repo names are exposed).
#
# Create a classic PAT with read access to repositories:
#   https://github.com/settings/tokens  (scope: repo  →  read is enough)
# Or a fine-grained token with "Contents: Read-only" on the repos you want counted.
#
# Local dev: copy this file to `.env` (already git-ignored) and fill it in.
# Cloudflare Pages: add GITHUB_TOKEN under Settings → Environment variables,
#   then trigger a new build. Without it, the page falls back to the heatmap.
GITHUB_TOKEN=
